content.raw: ohhh I see. Forget my comment ;)

I think it's the magic macro in `cmake/GazeboTestUtils` that tries to generate an executable based on a class name which already exists. We could modify the macro to add the namespace to the test executable name, e.g. `UNIT_RENDERING_Conversions_TEST` but that's a lot of typing to run a test..
content.html: I think it's the magic macro in cmake/GazeboTestUtils that tries to generate an executable based on a class name which already exists. We could modify the macro to add the namespace to the test executable name, e.g. UNIT_RENDERING_Conversions_TEST but that's a lot of typing to run a test..
